    <!-- SLIDE 3: Introduction -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-3" data-bg="backgrounds/shopping-cart.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>When a mysterious sound rips through a Las Vegas superstore and delivers disturbing visions to the shoppers inside, it splits them into believers and skeptics—and saints and killers.</p>
          <p>Mixing cosmic horror with the painfully human desire for answers, <em><strong>Static</strong></em> is an eight-episode series that welds the spiritualized concerns of <em>The Leftovers</em> to a <em>Fugitive</em>-style thriller.</p>
          <p>This neon-soaked mystery invites viewers to speculate on the sound&rsquo;s origins alongside characters who go down very different roads as they search for meaning in a fallen world. Some will fight to restore what was lost, while others think it&rsquo;s time to clear the stage for a better show.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 4: The Sound -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-4" data-bg="backgrounds/close-encounters.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>There&rsquo;s a hum in the distance, and a few shoppers cock their heads, thinking it might be a siren or some machinery on the fritz. Then the sliding doors shatter, and a vicious frequency howls through the superstore, a teeth-grinding drone that rearranges the lives of everyone inside.</p>
          <p>A cab driver sees the bloody wreckage of her past. A cashier is tormented by the love he abandoned. An internet superstar receives a message from beyond. Seventy-one customers are vacant-eyed and swaying, teetering on the edge of the unknown. A lucky few experience visions of transcendence, even revelation—but not the priest who cowers in the frozen food aisle, horrified by a childhood monster that has come to life.</p>
          <p>When the cameras arrive, the survivors provide conflicting accounts as they shiver beneath shock blankets, saying it was the sound of a dial tone or maybe a demon. Some think it&rsquo;s a new form of weather. Others say it&rsquo;s the latest style of terror. And a growing number are beginning to believe it&rsquo;s the voice of God.</p>
          <p>The cab driver thinks it was just her imagination until she hears a voice in the radio static, and it sounds just like her daughter who died in a baffling accident six years ago.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 5: The Story (part 1) -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-5" data-bg="backgrounds/coals.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>As the otherworldly sound fades into the Vegas night, a cab driver (KAY, 60s) flees the scene. She&rsquo;s got an outstanding warrant and, more importantly, she&rsquo;s seen what superstition does to people, and it&rsquo;s not pretty. But then she hears her daughter (CARLY DEE, 30s) on the radio, a one-hit-wonder who died in an infamous accident—and she&rsquo;s calling out for her mother.</p>
          <p>Meanwhile, a charismatic priest (FATHER JIM, 40s) who thinks God mocked him in the superstore, will retreat into the desert and conjure a new religion from the footage of a sitcom. He becomes obsessed with rewinding time and restoring order to his world, and he&rsquo;ll start by proving the sound was a hallucination and nothing more.</p>
          <p>As the ruins of the store become a makeshift town for the survivors and the curious alike, a cashier (EDDIE, 30s) will transform his grief into a gift. Two internet celebrities (SILVER and GOLD, 20s) will profoundly diverge as they search for answers. And a man known only as THE MANAGER (30s) will purchase the property, hoping people will gamble on an encounter with the divine.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 6: The Story (part 2) -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-6" data-bg="backgrounds/in-the-mood-for-love.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>Like a modern-day siren, Carly Dee&rsquo;s voice in the static will draw these people into a world where the familiar becomes unreal, a world of ceremonial car crashes and horrifying makeup tutorials, of crowds laying down on the interstate and towers of home appliances looming above the sprawl. A line from a ballad becomes a prophecy—<em>you can hear better in the dark</em>—and, as Carly Dee&rsquo;s devotees gather to await the return of the Great Frequency, the lights of Vegas begin to flicker.</p>
          <p>If Kay wants to reach her daughter and reveal the mystery of the Great Frequency, she must reckon with her own dark past. And she will need everyone&rsquo;s help to stop Father Jim, who is determined to remove all evidence of the sound—and destroy anyone who&rsquo;s heard it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

