        <div class="character__text">
          <h3 class="character__name">Kay</h3>
          <p class="character__age">60s</p>
          <p>A jittery and sharp-tongued Taiwanese-American woman, Kay grinds away in the gig economy, ferrying drunks around Vegas at night and scrubbing images from the internet during the day.</p>
          <p>She&rsquo;s seen what humanity has to offer, and she knows there&rsquo;s nothing worth believing in, not on this planet or anywhere else. Of course she&rsquo;s resentful: she&rsquo;d been a star in her youth, an Olympic diver whose dreams were cut short by tragedy after tragedy, culminating in her daughter&rsquo;s death six years ago. But she won&rsquo;t talk about her past or even tell you her real name. If she did, she might have to explain why her daughter hated her—and why she sometimes sees an old man falling from the sky.</p>
          <p>Now her dead daughter is on the radio, claiming responsibility for the otherworldly sound that haunts the shoppers at a superstore. As Kay searches for the source of her child&rsquo;s voice, she will become a fugitive, drawn into a world of bizarre rituals and the glare of television cameras. This cynical woman who spent her life keeping her head down, believing in nothing, will find herself becoming a leader. But if she wants to save her new community, she&rsquo;ll need to face up to her past—and atone.</p>
          <p class="character__cf">cf. Michelle Yeoh, Joan Chen, Christine Hakim</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 9: Father Jim -->
    <section class="slide slide--character" id="slide-9" data-bg-color="#000">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content slide__content--split">
        <div class="character__portrait">
          <img src="{{asset "img/static/portraits/priest.webp"}}" alt="Father Jim — character portrait" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="character__text">
          <h3 class="character__name">Father Jim</h3>
          <p class="character__age">40s</p>
          <p>A chatty priest from New Orleans with a smile that could charm the devil, Father Jim is beloved by his community—and he loves being their leader. After encountering pure evil as a child, he&rsquo;s spent fifty years on the righteous path, and he knows he&rsquo;s right with God. He&rsquo;d always imagined that if the moment ever came, he&rsquo;d be first in line to receive divine judgment, and he would do it with his eyes cast up to heaven, ready to take his place in the drama of the ancients. But now the Lord has played him for a fool, leaving him writhing in torment while others experienced holy ecstasy.</p>
          <p>Although his faith has been shattered, Father Jim will pick up the pieces, the few he can find anyway, and he will conjure a new and better God, one who guides him to a new flock in the most unlikely of places. And he will transform an old sitcom into a gospel that will lead him towards the very evil that fascinated him as a boy: a creature in the shadows, swinging a massive mallet and hunting for anything that might bleed.</p>
          <p class="character__cf">cf. Matthew Goode, Lee Pace, Jon Hamm</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 10: Carly Dee -->
    <section class="slide slide--character" id="slide-10" data-bg-color="#000">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content slide__content--split">
        <div class="character__portrait">
          <img src="{{asset "img/static/portraits/carly-dee.webp"}}" alt="Carly Dee — character portrait" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="character__text">
          <h3 class="character__name">Carly Dee</h3>
          <p class="character__age">30s</p>
          <p>Kay&rsquo;s daughter had been a happy girl who dreamed of seeing her name in lights. But she was forever changed the night an otherworldly sound filled her head on a remote Iowa road. When her mother denied it happened, Carly Dee ran away as soon as she could, determined to find some answers. Instead, she found a career as an avant-garde rock-n-roller who invented &ldquo;celestial metal&rdquo; and became a one-hit-wonder with a song about how &ldquo;you can hear better in the dark.&rdquo; But if she&rsquo;s remembered at all these days, it&rsquo;s only as &ldquo;the girl in the car&rdquo; when a beloved actor-turned-politician plowed his Cadillac into a boulder, killing them both.</p>
          <p>Some of her die-hard fans think she&rsquo;s the voice on the radio, the mysterious woman known as the Voice of the Red Rocks who hijacked the airwaves and predicted the cosmic sound that tore up a Vegas superstore. She&rsquo;s being hailed as a prophet, even if she died six years ago. Is she a ghost in the machine, leading the desperate and damaged into a dangerous new faith? Is she really causing the lights of Vegas to flicker? Carly Dee is our Colonel Kurtz in <em>Apocalypse Now</em>, the riddle in the shadows that will draw her mother up the river into a confrontation that might turn out the lights for good.</p>
          <p class="character__cf">cf. Gemma Chan, Greta Lee, Dichen Lachman</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 11: Tanner Whitney -->
    <section class="slide slide--character" id="slide-11" data-bg-color="#000">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content slide__content--split">
        <div class="character__portrait">
          <img src="{{asset "img/static/portraits/tanner-whitney.webp"}}" alt="Tanner Whitney — character portrait" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="character__text">
          <h3 class="character__name">Tanner Whitney</h3>
          <p class="character__age">40s</p>
          <p>&ldquo;You&rsquo;ll never know what time it is!&rdquo; Cut to a mischievous grin as sixteen-year-old Tanner Whitney delivers his famous catchphrase on <em>Family Therapy</em>, the sitcom everyone knows, even if they never watched it intentionally. Whitney was a child star who became a national sensation when he traded the soundstage for the soapbox, summoning the energy of Bobby Kennedy on cocaine as he beamed before rapt crowds who chanted, &ldquo;We <em>know</em> what time it is!&rdquo; Then he met a notorious musician named Carly Dee. Later that night, his car was found wrapped around a boulder in the desert.</p>
          <p>The tragic end of Tanner Whitney&rsquo;s life has transformed him into a myth. But some folks refuse to let him go. <em>That wasn&rsquo;t his body,</em> they say. <em>The funeral was a deep-fake.</em> Every Sunday night, they gather in the desert to reenact Whitney&rsquo;s last moments and marvel at the airbag that, like the Veil of Veronica, bears an imprint of his face.</p>
          <p>And then one night, an odd priest interrupts this ritual and begins to reshape Whitney&rsquo;s image—and the footage from his TV show—into a frightening weapon in a war against God.</p>
          <p class="character__cf">cf. James Marsden, Michael Ealy, Henry Cavill</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 12: Leo, Gold, Silver -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-12" data-bg="backgrounds/diner.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="char-grid glass-panel glass-panel--full">
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>Leo</h3>
            <p class="character__age">40s</p>
            <p>A jolly lumberjack of a man who writes unpublishable fantasy novels when he&rsquo;s not working the swing shift as a cashier, Leo got sober by putting his faith in other people. But now that everyone around him has gone a little crazy, he&rsquo;ll need to find another higher power if he wants to avoid slipping back into his past. And it might require helping Kay make her own leap of faith.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>Gold</h3>
            <p class="character__age">20s</p>
            <p>Born into a deeply evangelical family in Arkansas, Gold has always associated faith with poverty. And she wants nothing to do with either. After parlaying her good looks into a lucrative influencer gig with the help of her partner Silver (and a few shady foreign banks), Gold is determined to stay on the air, no matter what comes her way. For her, the superstore parking lot is the bleeding edge where the world is shifting and cracking, transforming into something new. And she&rsquo;s the star of it all—as long as she keeps her investors happy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>Silver</h3>
            <p class="character__age">20s</p>
            <p>A brilliant programmer from Ohio, Silver was looking for a change of scenery when she replied to Gold&rsquo;s job posting for a digital assistant. Before she knew it, she became Gold&rsquo;s partner in crime, the two of them delivering investment advice for an audience of millions. As the money rolled in, Silver spent lavishly, never asking questions. But after encountering a cosmic truth at the superstore, she&rsquo;s beginning to question everything, much to Gold&rsquo;s chagrin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 13: The Manager, Chuck, Ruby -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-13" data-bg="backgrounds/elisha-terada.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="char-grid glass-panel glass-panel--full">
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>The Manager</h3>
            <p class="character__age">30s</p>
            <p>When the authorities clash with the survivors who refuse to leave the ruins of the superstore, a stranger in a cowboy hat strides over, clutching the deed to the property. He just bought the place, and he decides who stays and who goes. For now, the survivors can stay because they'll help him make this dump bigger than Caesar&rsquo;s. Who wouldn&rsquo;t want to gamble on a visit with God? The Manager is the reason for the proverb &ldquo;a merchant has no mother country,&rdquo; but his love of profit is challenged when he forms an unexpected bond.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>Chuck</h3>
            <p class="character__age">40s</p>
            <p>A man-child who spends his life in stained sweatpants and flip-flops, Chuck gave up on the world long ago. He might look dim, but he was bright enough to see the writing on the wall: a future of fire, floods, and viruses. So why not spend his life on the sofa, covered in cheez dust? But a quick run to the superstore left him with a vision that transforms him into a media sensation—and a beacon of hope for the disillusioned.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="char-col">
            <h3>Ruby</h3>
            <p class="character__age">50s</p>
            <p>Her sanity is hanging by the thinnest thread, but Ruby&rsquo;s doing her best to survive out here in the 21st century, guiding tourists to a secret ritual at the foot of Black Mountain in exchange for a few dollars and a can of High Life. &ldquo;I try to follow the example of Christ,&rdquo; Ruby tells them. &ldquo;The real deal, not that steeple horseshit—I&rsquo;m talking &rsquo;bout the Jesus who lived with the junkies and leopards.&rdquo; But she does keep a straight razor in the folds of her dress...</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 14: Black Sunshine / Cosmic Membrane -->
    <section class="slide slide--lyrics" id="slide-14" data-bg-color="#0a0a0a">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="lyrics-quote">&ldquo;But none of these thoughts are mine,<br>they belong to the black sunshine.<br>So close your eyes when we&rsquo;re apart,<br>because you can hear better in the dark.&rdquo;</div>
        <div class="lyrics-attribution">—Carly Dee, &ldquo;Black Sunshine&rdquo;</div>
        <div class="lyrics-content">
          <div class="lyrics-content__album">
            <img src="{{asset "img/static/albums/cosmic-membrane.webp"}}" alt="Cosmic Membrane album cover" loading="lazy">
            <p class="lyrics-content__caption">The iconic cover of Carly Dee&rsquo;s album <em>Cosmic Membrane</em>, an unlistenable record that her die-hard fans believe foretold the Great Frequency.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="lyrics-content__text">
            <p>They call themselves her &ldquo;shadows,&rdquo; these women and men dressed in black with streaks of glittery black paint running down their faces. And more of them are following her instructions on the radio and walking away from their lives to gather in parking lots and highways, where they&rsquo;re making plans to turn out the lights of Vegas and hasten the return of the Great Frequency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 15: Structure -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-15" data-bg="backgrounds/asphalt.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel glass-panel--full">
          <p class="structure-intro">Each episode beyond the pilot will have a self-contained arc that begins with the vision one of our characters experienced in the superstore, allowing us to explore their backstory and the reasons for the decisions they&rsquo;re about to make.</p>
          <div class="acts-grid">
            <div class="act-col">
              <h4>ACT I: The Sound</h4>
              <p>Episodes 1-3 depict the first mass encounter with &ldquo;the sound&rdquo; and its impact on each character we meet at the superstore. Driven from his church, Father Jim will establish a new religion that uses footage from a sitcom as its gospel. Leo will create a recovery group that goes in an unexpected direction. Once an inseparable team, Silver and Gold&rsquo;s search for a plausible explanation will leave them changed in very different ways. And Kay will discover the ghost of her daughter, Carly Dee, has been hijacking the airwaves, predicting &ldquo;the Great Frequency&rdquo;—and some think she&rsquo;s a prophet.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="act-col">
              <h4>ACT II: The Ballad</h4>
              <p>Episodes 4-6 find our characters returning to the ruins of the superstore after failing to reconnect with their lives &ldquo;before.&rdquo; A makeshift town emerges, thanks to the benevolence of the new owner, a mysterious investor who bought the place in cash. Despite wanting to remain a loner, Kay finds herself becoming a leader—until Carly Dee broadcasts Kay&rsquo;s dark past for everyone to hear. Silver will leave Kay&rsquo;s side to join Carly Dee&rsquo;s &ldquo;shadows.&rdquo; As she gathers a larger and more fervent flock, we will delve into Carly Dee&rsquo;s story—and perhaps take her side against her mother. Meanwhile, Father Jim is hoping for a great reset, and he&rsquo;s determined to erase everyone who&rsquo;s heard the sound.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="act-col">
              <h4>ACT III: The Tower</h4>
              <p>Episodes 7-8 bring us into the monastery of Carly Dee&rsquo;s shadows. A strip mall transformed into the opposite of Kay&rsquo;s shabby community at the superstore, it&rsquo;s a stark yet functional society of ascetic ritual that has turned its back on the modern world. Meanwhile, Gold&rsquo;s media empire and Father Jim&rsquo;s flock fuse into a powerful new force. Soon these factions will be drawn towards a climax that finds a frightening army bearing down upon Kay&rsquo;s new community, forcing her to atone for her past before she can enlist the help of others. As the lights of Vegas flicker, she must summon her daughter so she can stop this madness before the lights go out forever.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 16: Location — Las Vegas -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-16" data-bg="backgrounds/desert-city.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>Set in the near future, <em>Static</em> is an American fable inspired by two locations:</p>
          <h4 class="location-sub">Las Vegas</h4>
          <p>A hallucinatory city where people gather to exploit each other and be exploited—what better place to explore the collision between our darkest urges and our desire for meaning? The Strip will remain a throb in the distance; we&rsquo;re more interested in the fringes of the sprawl, where Vegas has become a polyglot church of strip malls, jumbotrons, night markets, and ad-hoc communities from all corners of the world.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 17: Location — Mojave Desert -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-17" data-bg="backgrounds/joshua-trees.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <h4 class="location-sub">The Mojave Desert</h4>
          <p>Since the beginning of history, the desert has been the home of revelation, a geography of desperate saints and ascetics dragging themselves across the sand in search of salvation. This energy reverberates through today&rsquo;s American desert, where airplane graveyards glint in the sun, people search the sky for flying saucers, and there&rsquo;s a woman who can tell your future by deciphering the contrails of military aircraft.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 18: Location — Three Locations -->
    <section class="slide" id="slide-18" data-bg="backgrounds/neon-barn.webp">
      <div class="slide__bg"></div>
      <div class="slide__content">
        <div class="glass-panel">
          <p>Our story unfolds along the borderlands of the city and the desert, where streetlights give way to darkness. We will spend most of our time in three locations:</p>
          <div class="location-body">
            <h4 class="location-sub">The Superstore</h4>
